home.name: I'm Retta El Sayed.
home.description: The idea of applying engineering concepts to medicine has been always fascinating to me. My research interest in cardiovascular fluid mechanics stems from their potential to provide accurate patient-specific diagnoses, prediction of surgical procedure outcomes, and application to a wide variety of biomedical problems. I have worked on projects that have the potential to improve human quality of life by conducting a non-invasive means to understand blood flow hemodynamics. Through these projects, I gained experience in 4D Flow magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) and computational fluid dynamics (CFD). I mostly enjoy working on multidisciplinary projects, which led me to work with many collaborators to apply engineering concepts to clinical applications.

testimonials.name: Steve Jobs
testimonials.description: Your work is going to fill a large part of your life, and the only way to be truly satisfied is to do what you believe is great work. And the only way to do great work is to love what you do. If you haven't found it yet, keep looking. Don't settle. As with all matters of the heart, you'll know when you find it.
